ent antics with Booth and her rejection of Booth's marriage proposal.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=28\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title=The Girl in Suite 2103\n |WrittenBy=Christopher Ambrose\n |DirectedBy=[[Karen Gaviola]]\n |Viewers=8.10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=101006_05|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=October 10, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2012}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|10|4}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY06\n |ShortSummary=Brennan and Booth are called to the site of an explosion in a Miami hotel where several people were either injured or killed, including an unidentified body found burned, thought to be the bomber. Initially, the explosion is thought to be the work of a Colombian drug cartel intending to target Judge Dolores Ramos, the Colombian judicial representative, who survived the blast. Diplomatic immunity and State Department official Alex Radziwill stand in way of Brennan and Booth's investigation as they pursue key clues about the case.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=29\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=The Girl with the Curl\n |WrittenBy=Karine Rosenthal\n |DirectedBy=[[Thomas J. Wright]]\n |Viewers=7.33<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=110706_05|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=November 7, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sTeeRmC9?url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=110706_05|archivedate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|11|1}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY07\n |ShortSummary=Brennan and Booth investigate the death of Brianna Swanson, a young beauty queen whose decomposed remains are discovered at a water filtration plant. Brianna's father is the initial suspect, but new clues lead elsewhere. Brennan and Booth investigate Brianna's dance school, where they find new information leading to several suspects. Meanwhile, Hodgins works up the nerve to ask Angela out on a date. At first, she rejects due to their situation as co-workers but after seeking advice from Brennan and Cam, she agrees to go.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=30\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=The Woman in the Sand\n |WrittenBy=[[Elizabeth Benjamin]]\n |DirectedBy=[[Kate Woods]]\n |Viewers=7.52<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=111406_09|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=November 14, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sTegBC2f?url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=111406_09|archivedate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|11|8}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY08\n |ShortSummary=The team head to the outskirts of [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] to investigate the murder of a missing federal prosecutor and a related murder of a female boxer. While questioning a suspect at a casino, Booth finds himself face to face with his old addiction: gambling. He and Bones go undercover as a couple to infiltrate an underground fight circuit to find out who or what got the victims killed.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=31\n |EpisodeNumber2=9\n |Title=Aliens in a Spaceship\n |WrittenBy=[[Janet Tamaro]]\n |DirectedBy=[[Craig Ross, Jr.]]\n |Viewers=7.83<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=112106_06|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=November 21, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sTejEbwz?url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=112106_06|archivedate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|11|15}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY09\n |ShortSummary=The team investigate the murder of two kidnapped teenage twin boys.  The boys were placed in a spaceship-like capsule and buried alive underground. Soon, Brennan and Hodgins find themselves victims of the \"Grave Digger\", and Booth frantically searches for them as they slowly run out of oxygen underground. The case as broadcast has no conclusion (it was solved in the season 4 episode \"The Hero in the Hold\"). The Fox Network website initially displayed a summary for the episode which included an original ending where the Grave Digger was identified as the female reporter that coauthored a book about Grave Digger.<ref>{{Cite web\n |title=Aliens in a Spaceship |url=http://www.fox.com/bones/episodes/recaps/209.htm\n |work=Bones Episode Recaps |publisher=[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] |date=November 2006\n |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20061117035053/http://www.fox.com/bones/episodes/recaps/209.htm |archivedate=November 17, 2006 |quote=''Brennan and Hodgins are pulled to the surface. Later, Brennan shows Booth the toll road sticker she found in Hodgins\u2019 leg. They run it and it links them to Janine O\u2019Connell. They arrest her and the case is closed.''}}</ref> The summary was later revised to reflect the episode as broadcast in which the Grave Digger is unidentified and the scene replaced by character reunion moments.<ref>{{Cite web\n |title=Aliens in a Spaceship |url=http://www.fox.com/bones/episodes/recaps/209.htm\n |work=Bones Episode Recaps |publisher=FOX |date=November 2006\n |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20061128235815/http://www.fox.com/bones/episodes/recaps/209.htm |archivedate=November 28, 2006 |quote=''Brennan and Hodgins are pulled to the surface, but the Grave Digger is still at large\u2026''}}</ref>\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=32\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=The Headless Witch in the Woods\n |WrittenBy=Stephen Nathan & Karine Rosenthal\n |DirectedBy=Tony Wharmby\n |Viewers=8.66<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=120506_08|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=December 5, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229221915/http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=120506_08|archivedate=February 29, 2012}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|11|29}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY10\n |ShortSummary=Brennan and Booth investigate when a headless corpse is found in the woods along with a frightening video tape of events on the night of the murder. Meanwhile, Hodgins and Angela are assigned to find any possible information on the video, much to Hodgins' glee, as Angela grasps his arm out of fear of what she sees. The episode's plot is a slight parody of the famous found-footage horror film, ''The Blair Witch Project'', with even the famous antagonist (the Blair Witch) of the film, presented as a legend in this episode (referred to here as \"Maggie Cinders\"). The murder suspects claim that \"Maggie\" killed the victim, and Brennan even finds a second, unidentified head that seems to corroborate that claim. At the end of the episode, after the killer is caught, Hodgins and Angela are relieved to turn off the video, but then they notice the silhouette of a headless female figure with an axe heading toward the victim right before he was killed. Freaked out, they both offer probably correct and rational theories explaining it, with Angela fearfully asking Hodgins at the end, \"Can I stay at your place tonight?\", much to Hodgins' obvious pleasure.  \n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=33\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=Judas on a Pole\n |WrittenBy=Hart Hanson\n |DirectedBy=[[David Duchovny]]\n |Viewers=8.62<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yourentertainmentnow.com/2006/12/14/broadcast-tv-ratings-for-wednesday-december-13-2006/|title=Broadcast TV Ratings for Wednesday, December 13, 2006|work=Your Entertainment Now|date=December 14, 2006|accessdate=December 17, 2012}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|12|13}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY11\n |ShortSummary=Zack defends his dissertation to obtain his doctorate and asks help from a colleague. Meanwhile, Booth and Brennan are called to the scene where a man's body was found gutted, burned and hung like a scarecrow on the roof of a hotel that housed Federal witnesses. Booth determines the victim was a snitch working in an organized crime syndicate. Brennan's brother, Russ, informs her of a phone call he received from their father, warning him they are both in danger. Soon after, a priest contacts Brennan telling her that her father insists she and Booth drop their case. They determine the body found was actually an ex-FBI agent, tracking Russ to kill him \u2014 hence explaining the warning from Brennan's father. With the help of Angela, Booth and the team uncover a decades-old cover-up that could potentially ruin his career if he decides to continue with the investigation.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=34\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=The Man in the Cell\n |WrittenBy=Noah Hawley\n |DirectedBy=Jes\u00fas Trevi\u00f1o \n |Viewers=12.40<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=020607_05|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=February 6, 2007|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sTf0gI3Y?url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=020607_05|archivedate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|1|31}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY12\n |ShortSummary=Booth and Brennan are ordered to the cell of serial killer Howard Epps to identify the remains of an inmate. To their surprise, the charred remains don't belong to Epps. It's soon learned Epps has escaped and is on a revenge path, which involves Booth's young son, Parker. Due to the danger of the case, Brennan must get FBI protection. Cam inhales a toxin while performing an autopsy, which puts her life in danger.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=35\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=The Girl in the Gator\n |WrittenBy=Scott Williams\n |DirectedBy=[[Allan Kroeker]]\n |Viewers=12.57<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=021307_05|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=February 13, 2007|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sTf28D4U?url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=021307_05|archivedate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|7}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY13\n |ShortSummary=When Booth is ordered to go see a psychiatrist (guest star [[Stephen Fry]]) after irrationally discharging his firearm (at the clown on the top of an ice cream truck), Brennan is paired up with Agent Tim Sullivan to investigate the apparent murder of a college student in the Everglades, and by the time the case is solved Sullivan and Brennan express their mutual interest in each other.\n |LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 2)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=36\n |EpisodeNumber2=14\n |Title=The Man in the Mansion\n |WrittenBy=Christopher Ambrose\n |DirectedBy=[[Dwight Little]]\n |Viewers=12.28<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=022107_05|title=Weekly Program Rankings|work=ABC Medianet|date=February 21, 2007|accessdate=December 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5sTf3b94F?url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=022107_05|archivedate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|14}}\n |ProdCode=2AKY14\n |ShortSummary=When a benefactor of the Jeffer